domain_prompt:
DOMAIN BRIEF

# Summary
This domain models transporting packages within and between cities using trucks and airplanes. Trucks move between locations inside the same city, while airplanes fly between airports. Packages can be loaded into and unloaded from trucks and airplanes. Each action increases the total-cost.

# Object Types
- package: Base object
- truck: Base object
- airplane: Base object
- city: Base object
- location: Base object

# Predicates & Functions
- at-package: Package ?p is located at location ?l.
- at-truck: Truck ?t is located at location ?l.
- at-airplane: Airplane ?a is located at location ?l.
- in-truck: Package ?p is inside truck ?t.
- in-airplane: Package ?p is inside airplane ?a.
- in-city: Location ?l is inside city ?c.
- airport: Location ?l is an airport.
- total-cost: A numeric function representing the cumulative cost; actions increase this value.

# Actions

## Action: drive-truck
- Parameters: ?t (truck), ?from (location), ?to (location), ?c (city)
- Preconditions:
  - at-truck ?t is at location ?from.
  - in-city ?from is in city ?c.
  - in-city ?to is in city ?c.
- Effects:
  - It is no longer the case that at-truck ?t is at location ?from.
  - at-truck ?t is at location ?to.
  - Increase total-cost by 1.

## Action: fly-airplane
- Parameters: ?a (airplane), ?from (location), ?to (location)
- Preconditions:
  - at-airplane ?a is at location ?from.
  - airport ?from holds; the location ?from is an airport.
  - airport ?to holds; the location ?to is an airport.
- Effects:
  - It is no longer the case that at-airplane ?a is at location ?from.
  - at-airplane ?a is at location ?to.
  - Increase total-cost by 1.

## Action: load-truck
- Parameters: ?p (package), ?t (truck), ?l (location)
- Preconditions:
  - at-package ?p is at location ?l.
  - at-truck ?t is at location ?l.
- Effects:
  - It is no longer the case that at-package ?p is at location ?l.
  - in-truck ?p is inside truck ?t.
  - Increase total-cost by 1.

## Action: unload-truck
- Parameters: ?p (package), ?t (truck), ?l (location)
- Preconditions:
  - in-truck ?p is inside truck ?t.
  - at-truck ?t is at location ?l.
- Effects:
  - It is no longer the case that in-truck ?p is inside truck ?t.
  - at-package ?p is at location ?l.
  - Increase total-cost by 1.

## Action: load-airplane
- Parameters: ?p (package), ?a (airplane), ?l (location)
- Preconditions:
  - at-package ?p is at location ?l.
  - at-airplane ?a is at location ?l.
  - airport ?l holds; the location ?l is an airport.
- Effects:
  - It is no longer the case that at-package ?p is at location ?l.
  - in-airplane ?p is inside airplane ?a.
  - Increase total-cost by 1.

## Action: unload-airplane
- Parameters: ?p (package), ?a (airplane), ?l (location)
- Preconditions:
  - in-airplane ?p is inside airplane ?a.
  - at-airplane ?a is at location ?l.
- Effects:
  - It is no longer the case that in-airplane ?p is inside airplane ?a.
  - at-package ?p is at location ?l.
  - Increase total-cost by 1.

FINAL CHECK
- All action names are identical to the PDDL.
- All Lisp syntax is removed; conditions and effects are written in clear English.
- Preconditions and effects are fully and exactly captured, including numeric increases to total-cost.

actions.name: drive-truck
effects: TRUCK is no longer at FROM.

actions.name: load-truck
effects: PACKAGE is no longer at LOCATION.

actions.name: unload-truck
effects: PACKAGE is no longer inside TRUCK.

actions.name: fly-airplane
effects: PLANE is no longer at AIRPORT_FROM.

actions.name: load-airplane
effects: PACKAGE is no longer at AIRPORT.

actions.name: unload-airplane
effects: PACKAGE is no longer inside PLANE.
